        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 3:49PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Woodlawn, or near Marshall, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marshall, Jefferson, Karnack, Harleton, Woodlawn, Scottsville,
Nesbitt, and Leigh.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
